# TriCore

TriCore is an interactive platform for exploring ternary computing.

While modern computers use binary logic (0 and 1), ternary computing uses three possible states. This project explores how computer systems could be designed around ternary logic and provides tools for experimenting with ternary mathematics, logic gates, and processor concepts.

## Current Status

🚧 Early Development

The repository has been initialized and core project planning is underway. Development is currently focused on building the foundational components of the platform, beginning with ternary number systems and arithmetic.

## Features

* Ternary number conversion
* Balanced ternary calculations
* Ternary logic gate simulation
* Arithmetic visualization
* CPU and architecture experiments

